cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.GT, cs.CC. 

The paper deals with the problem of computing minimum dominating set for a given set of points in the plane, which is a classic problem in computational geometry and graph theory. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are the most likely categories. The paper also proposes approximation algorithms and a PTAS for the problem, which falls under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Finally, the paper proposes a shifting lemma, which is a general technique in computational geometry and can be applied to other problems as well, making cs.CC (Computational Complexity) a likely category as well.
